{
  "texts": [
    "In the gauge-fixing of the worldsheet metric, we introduce the c-ghost which has the same weight as the gauge parameter (a worldsheet vector field) but opposite statistics.",
    "Similarly, we introduce an additional ghost c of weight (-2,0) with fermionic statistics to gauge-fix Q.",
    "A putative BRST operator is thenQ = dz cT + cQ +...,(2.9)where T now includes ghost contributions and the +... accounts for terms present due to the fact that [T, cQ] ̸ = 0, as well as terms from M 4.",
    "It is difficult to understand what CFT the ghosts c live in.",
    "A way forward comes from considering the bosonization of the (b, c) ghost system,b(z) = e iσ(z), c(z) = e -iσ(z),where σ is a linear dilaton theory (appendix C) with stress tensorT σ = - 1 2 (∂σ) 2 + 3i 2 ∂ 2 σ, σ(z)σ(w) ∼ -ln(z -w).Naively, we can deduce the form of c by an analogous bosonization c = e mρ for some real m, where ρ is a linear dilaton with stress tensorT ρ = ϵ 1 2 (∂ρ) 2 - 1 2 q ρ ∂ 2 ρ, ρ(z)ρ(w) ∼ ϵ ln(z -w).In order to cancel the conformal anomaly, we would like c to carry a central charge of +28."
  ]
}